            <abstract>
                <gco:CharacterString>The Zoning By-law regulates the use of land such as residential, commercial, industrial or institutional, as well as the location, size and height of buildings or structures, built form, sets out parking and loading requirements and other site specific requirements. Learn more about Zoning By-laws in HamiltonWhile every attempt is made to keep zoning information up to date, the City of Hamilton does not accept any responsibility for the accuracy of this information. Any reliance upon this information shall be at your own risk. Accordingly, verification of actual zoning for a particular property or properties must be obtained by way of a Zoning Verification Certificate from the City of Hamilton.</gco:CharacterString>
            </abstract>
            <purpose>
                <gco:CharacterString>Zoning polygon boundaries that regulate permitted uses of land in Hamilton.</gco:CharacterString>
            </purpose>
